\subsection{The Definitions}

In this first formalisation of the concept of analyticity we construe a truth conditional semantics as a function which for any sentence delivers the property of conditions which is true of those conditions under which the sentence is true.

A sentence is analytic if its value under the semantics is the property of conditions whcih is always true. 

